ANCYL deputy president Desmond Moela says that the accused should have reported Rethabile Mlotshwa's alleged trespassing to the police. JOHANNESBURG The African National Congress Youth League (ANCYL) says the two men accused of assaulting Rethabile Mlotshwa in an apparent racist attack, should have reported Mlotshwa to the police if they were concerned about trespassing.A video showing Mlotshwa forced to lie in a coffin has gone viral. ANCYL deputy president Desmond Moela addressed scores of party supporters outside the Middelburg Magistrate's Court today.Moela says Willem Oosthuizen and Theo Jacobs should have known better.WATCH: Coffin video leads to criminal charges If the victim has trespassed their property, we have a law in this country. He says Mlotshwa is an ANC member, and the Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) and the Democratic Alliance (DA) also present at the court appearance , are just trying to score political points. EFF and DA are just clowns. These are just political prostitute parties. He says his party will support Mlotshwa and his family, to help them through their ordeal.WATCH: Coffin assault case postponed(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)